1
00:00:34,509 --> 00:00:36,469
Pirates!

2
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:39,179
Attack!

3
00:00:39,380 --> 00:00:42,710
When he was a little boy,
Dae Ju was his favorite friend.

4
00:00:43,450 --> 00:00:45,850
And the person he loved the most
was his mother.

5
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:46,850
Mom.

6
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:49,020
- Did you have fun?
- Mom.

7
00:00:56,289 --> 00:00:57,799
Mom is angry.

8
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,469
Ms. Choi. Ms. Lee.

9
00:01:00,469 --> 00:01:01,969
How is Min Ik's birthday party
planning going?

10
00:01:02,070 --> 00:01:03,740
- We're working on it, Ma'am.
- We're working on it, Ma'am.

11
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,310
What did you say
you wanted for your birthday?

12
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,349
A boat.

13
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:18,549
He thought it was going to be
an awesome birthday party.

14
00:01:21,349 --> 00:01:24,519
(Happy 7th birthday, Do Min Ik!)

15
00:01:25,019 --> 00:01:27,560
Until he saw the real boat.

16
00:01:40,510 --> 00:01:42,040
Here. You can have it.

17
00:01:43,010 --> 00:01:45,209
I'm tired of it now.

18
00:01:46,579 --> 00:01:47,680
Really?

19
00:01:50,109 --> 00:01:52,079
Then what should I do with that?

20
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:57,560
Then let's use it
as our secret place.

21
00:01:57,859 --> 00:02:01,129
When we have secrets
we want to share with each other,

22
00:02:01,129 --> 00:02:03,629
let's meet at There, Boat There.

23
00:02:03,859 --> 00:02:04,930
Okay.

24
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:12,169
Seriously!

25
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:17,080
Ms. Jeong.

26
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:19,639
Help...

27
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:22,479
Save me, please.

28
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:25,219
What? Why...

29
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:28,090
Why should I...

30
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:32,189
Min Ik!

31
00:02:32,389 --> 00:02:33,460
Ms. Jeong.

32
00:02:35,090 --> 00:02:36,360
Wait a second!

33
00:02:36,729 --> 00:02:38,699
Okay, go, go!

34
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,900
Min Ik.

35
00:02:45,469 --> 00:02:46,500
Min Ik!

36
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,169
What... What's wrong?

37
00:03:21,939 --> 00:03:22,939
What?

38
00:03:26,509 --> 00:03:27,710
Is it back?

39
00:03:28,449 --> 00:03:31,949
Yes, I came back
because I felt so upset.

40
00:03:31,949 --> 00:03:34,219
Right? It's back, right?

41
00:03:34,419 --> 00:03:37,020
No, I'm not back for you.

42
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,759
I'm back to clear my name.

43
00:03:42,229 --> 00:03:44,460
I'm back to clear my name!
Not to see you get undressed!

44
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:46,360
- My dress shirt.
- Okay.

45
00:03:50,199 --> 00:03:51,400
Darn it.

46
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:57,909
Are you allowed to leave
the hospital?

47
00:03:58,539 --> 00:03:59,610
I need to go somewhere.

48
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,250
Me too.

49
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,150
Hello.

50
00:04:07,449 --> 00:04:08,689
Where to?

51
00:04:08,689 --> 00:04:10,150
- Tanhyun Studio.
- Yeongdeungpo Police Station.

52
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:12,389
Have you ever seen me
miss an appointment?

53
00:04:12,389 --> 00:04:14,360
Have you ever seen a secretary
who got fired go to work?

54
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,360
We need to go to the police station
and clear my name first.

55
00:04:19,699 --> 00:04:22,230
Then get out of the car.
I'll meet you there after work.

56
00:04:23,899 --> 00:04:25,199
What if you don't come?

57
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:30,610
Then get in.

58
00:04:30,910 --> 00:04:32,939
Are you going to stay or leave?

59
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:39,180
You promised to go to the police
right after the shoot, okay?

60
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:40,949
I won't run away, so just...

61
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:49,990
Director Do.

62
00:04:54,699 --> 00:04:55,730
Who is she?

63
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,839
Gosh, it's Eul Wang Lee.

64
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,939
I mean, it's Ms. Lee Eul Wang.

65
00:05:00,410 --> 00:05:01,470
That's her?

66
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,269
What are we going to do?

67
00:05:03,269 --> 00:05:04,610
She was even supposed to come...

68
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:08,180
to my goodbye party yesterday
because she heard I got fired.

69
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:14,720
Gal Hee, what are you doing here?

70
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:17,389
Well, the thing is,
I kind of had a situation.

71
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:21,529
- What about you? Why are you here?
- What?

72
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:27,329
Oh, well,
the director called my team...

73
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:30,439
because he couldn't reach
neither Director Do nor you.

74
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:35,170
Are you okay, Director Do?

75
00:05:37,379 --> 00:05:38,709
Yes, I'm okay.

76
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,550
You're here.

77
00:05:42,410 --> 00:05:43,750
Who is he?

78
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:46,279
Who do you think?
He's the video director.

79
00:05:48,319 --> 00:05:50,519
Hello. Why didn't you answer
any of my calls?

80
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:52,089
Everyone's waiting for you inside.

81
00:05:52,259 --> 00:05:53,290
Well...

82
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:56,829
I'll be waiting for you outside.

83
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:03,970
Don't go.

84
00:06:11,509 --> 00:06:12,779
From now on,

85
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,110
stay by my side...

86
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:21,290
no matter what happens, okay?

87
00:06:26,689 --> 00:06:29,930
Director Do,
please stand next to Da Young.

88
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,500
- Who is it?
- Pardon?

89
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,639
Who's Da Young?

90
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:41,209
Why are you asking me that?

91
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:46,439
Da Young, please raise your hand.

92
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:48,279
Yes, ma'am!

93
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:49,949
It's her.

94
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:53,420
Why do you keep asking me
who people are?

95
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,920
You're normally so good
at remembering people's faces.

96
00:07:03,259 --> 00:07:05,300
Okay, let's give it one more try.

97
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,730
You know what to do, right?
Okay, let's go.

98
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,000
Why does she keep calling me?

99
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,540
I'm sorry,
but I can't talk right now.

100
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:17,610
Are you in a detention center,
or did you just go missing?

101
00:07:17,610 --> 00:07:20,110
There are so many rumors
about what happened to you.

102
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,009
What took you so long
to answer your phone?

103
00:07:22,279 --> 00:07:24,680
It's more like I'm taken hostage.

104
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,560
Okay, great job.

105
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,089
You guys, this is really
going to be the last time.

106
00:07:34,089 --> 00:07:35,689
Get to your positions.

107
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,000
I need to get to my senses.

108
00:07:44,170 --> 00:07:45,800
I need to get to my senses.

109
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:54,079
Director Do?

110
00:08:12,699 --> 00:08:13,970
My gosh!

111
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:18,600
Director Do, where are you going?

112
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:20,569
The doors are opening.

113
00:08:22,639 --> 00:08:23,670
The doors are closing.

114
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:25,810
Are you purposely trying to make me
have a hard time?

115
00:08:26,709 --> 00:08:30,310
Didn't I... Didn't I tell you
to stay right by my side?

116
00:08:30,779 --> 00:08:32,379
Why are you angry at me?

117
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,490
Gosh, why are you sweating so much?

118
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:44,299
What is this?

119
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,330
What do you think? I'm Ms. Jeong,
the one who got fired yesterday.

120
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:50,129
The Jeong Gal Hee you fired
with a smile on your face.

121
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:52,799
I'm Jeong Gal Hee, the famous minion
of TnT Mobile!

122
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,340
Yes, I know that!

123
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,909
Secretary Jeong.

124
00:08:57,909 --> 00:08:59,279
Why are you the only one
who doesn't change?

125
00:09:00,309 --> 00:09:01,679
Yes, you're right.

126
00:09:01,679 --> 00:09:02,879
I got fired,

127
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:05,720
but I'm still being patient
and helping you out.

128
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,690
I can't believe I just wiped
the sweat off your face.

129
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:08,850
The doors are opening.

130
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:09,990
Dr. Gu.

131
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,360
I need to meet Dr. Gu first.

132
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:17,600
I knew you'd do this.

133
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:21,200
It's time to go see a detective,
not a doctor. You promised.

134
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,100
Your name, please.

135
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,039
Do Min Ik.

136
00:09:33,809 --> 00:09:36,110
Do Min Ik.

137
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:38,350
(Call 112 to report a crime.)

138
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:39,950
It's either 1 of the 2.

139
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,049
Either the world is going crazy...

140
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:47,559
- Address, please.
- Seocho-dong, Seoul.

141
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:49,259
Or I'm crazy.

142
00:09:49,259 --> 00:09:52,129
Excuse me. You're not him.

143
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:55,200
I'm asking him questions.
Why do you keep answering?

144
00:09:55,629 --> 00:09:57,740
I'm sorry. But...

145
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:01,240
He has trouble
memorizing his own address.

146
00:10:02,139 --> 00:10:03,710
Excuse me, sir.

147
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,549
Who were you supposed to meet
at the site of the incident?

148
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:08,879
My friend.

149
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:12,120
But he didn't show up
for some reason.

150
00:10:13,149 --> 00:10:14,519
Without even calling you?

151
00:10:14,519 --> 00:10:16,889
He didn't exactly need to call...

152
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:19,720
because we're close enough
to understand.

153
00:10:20,289 --> 00:10:21,360
I see.

154
00:10:22,389 --> 00:10:24,230
You said you saw
the criminal's face, right?

155
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,600
Yes.

156
00:10:27,299 --> 00:10:29,669
I definitely saw his face.

157
00:10:30,399 --> 00:10:32,269
Do you think you'll be able
to recognize him?

158
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,669
How did it go?

159
00:10:37,139 --> 00:10:38,179
Okay.

160
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:40,639
I'll go see you tomorrow, sir.

161
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:45,879
(Boss)

162
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:48,850
Even right now,
I remember his face vividly...

163
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:51,490
as if he's right next to me.

164
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:54,629
Here's the CCTV footage.

165
00:10:54,629 --> 00:10:56,230
Okay, let's see.

166
00:10:58,029 --> 00:11:01,200
It was really dark by the dock,
so nothing got caught on camera.

167
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:04,269
This one is a footage
from the parking lot.

168
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,039
Look.

169
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:09,210
It's him.

170
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:12,440
The guy wearing a black outfit
and a black hat.

171
00:11:13,580 --> 00:11:15,409
I can't see his face at all.

172
00:11:15,409 --> 00:11:16,950
- Rewind it a little.
- Okay.

173
00:11:21,649 --> 00:11:22,720
Stop.

174
00:11:28,690 --> 00:11:30,460
What's this?
You guys came in a group?

175
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:31,600
Well...

176
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,070
The secretaries overate.

177
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,830
So we wanted to work out. Look.

178
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,340
A golf club, a baseball bat...

179
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,470
They're all for sports.

180
00:11:41,669 --> 00:11:42,740
What about that jokbal?

181
00:11:43,309 --> 00:11:47,509
It's a great replacement
for dumbbells.

182
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:50,919
What... What is she saying?

183
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,350
- Zoom in.
- Okay.

184
00:11:55,190 --> 00:12:00,559
"I'm going to kill him."

185
00:12:00,690 --> 00:12:02,929
- She said "I'm going to kill him."
- What?

186
00:12:03,490 --> 00:12:05,129
Kill? Whom?

187
00:12:06,399 --> 00:12:07,399
Me?

188
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,940
I meant it's a killer view...

189
00:12:12,139 --> 00:12:14,710
and that I'm in such a good mood.

190
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:19,440
Let's not focus on this
and continue watching the footage.

191
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:24,850
Stop right there.

192
00:12:27,379 --> 00:12:28,389
Who's that?

193
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:31,090
What? Can't you tell who it is?

194
00:12:31,419 --> 00:12:32,490
Who is that?

195
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:37,029
Your colleague and best friend.

196
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,730
The friend you were there to meet.

197
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:45,840
Dae Ju?

198
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:52,909
11:53pm?

199
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:57,080
He was already there
when you arrived.

200
00:12:57,679 --> 00:13:01,019
Then where did he go
without meeting you first?

201
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,950
Not even a friend can be trusted.

202
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:13,700
(Honest and energetic
Yeongdeungpo Police)

203
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,299
Secretary Jeong,
how did you know about There?

204
00:13:16,570 --> 00:13:18,500
Boat There is Dae Ju and my
secret hide-out place.

205
00:13:18,769 --> 00:13:20,139
There's no such place...

206
00:13:20,139 --> 00:13:22,710
that is still only kept
between you two.

207
00:13:23,509 --> 00:13:26,080
Every one of yours
and Director Gi's secretaries...

208
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,679
know about Boat There.

209
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:32,580
I'm exhausted,
so let's head home for now.

210
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:35,250
Right, I should go home.

211
00:13:35,419 --> 00:13:36,990
Me, not you.

212
00:13:37,519 --> 00:13:39,960
I'm tired, so take me home.

213
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:44,529
You have money...

214
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:47,230
and you also have your own car.

215
00:13:47,799 --> 00:13:50,629
There's only one thing
you don't have though.

216
00:13:50,629 --> 00:13:52,269
As if that's possible.

217
00:13:53,340 --> 00:13:55,710
A secretary.

218
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:05,850
I did go there to kill you.

219
00:14:08,149 --> 00:14:10,590
You fired me even after
all the work I put in.

220
00:14:11,190 --> 00:14:12,690
I thought of my mom,

221
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:15,059
and it just made me so angry.

222
00:14:17,059 --> 00:14:19,460
Still, I ended up saving your life.

223
00:14:22,799 --> 00:14:26,139
This is my final act
as your secretary.

224
00:14:27,169 --> 00:14:29,039
I wasn't in a good place...

225
00:14:29,509 --> 00:14:31,379
to formally bid farewell
when you fired me.

226
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,379
Thank you for everything,

227
00:14:39,149 --> 00:14:40,580
Director Do.

228
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:56,970
Wait...

229
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:09,250
And here I thought
you had finally moved out.

230
00:15:17,659 --> 00:15:18,659
Uncle...

231
00:15:20,519 --> 00:15:21,860
It's you, right?

232
00:15:24,429 --> 00:15:25,500
Uncle?

233
00:15:26,330 --> 00:15:27,330
Not exactly.

234
00:15:27,669 --> 00:15:29,100
We're not actually related by blood.

235
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:37,009
Nonetheless, we did
swap saliva though.

236
00:15:37,809 --> 00:15:39,909
Since I was seven,
we ate soups and stews...

237
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:42,080
out of the same bowl.

238
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:50,190
Chirping like a cuckoo, are you?

239
00:15:50,190 --> 00:15:51,860
Don't call him that.

240
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,830
Min Ik is my son
whom I gave birth to.

241
00:15:57,799 --> 00:16:00,429
Are you even trying
to fool yourself now?

242
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,799
You took him in
while your husband was alive,

243
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:06,039
so you've done more than enough.

244
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,610
We let him take over for our dad,

245
00:16:09,610 --> 00:16:11,039
but he ran off with some young cow.

246
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,440
Are you announcing
how much of a fool I am?

247
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,750
Are you deliberately looking away?

248
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:40,299
Why must it be that face, Mom?

249
00:16:42,039 --> 00:16:43,070
You seem like...

250
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,909
the stranger I met...

251
00:16:48,049 --> 00:16:49,379
on my first day here.

252
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:02,090
Are you sick?

253
00:17:04,730 --> 00:17:05,859
Of course not.

254
00:17:07,799 --> 00:17:10,230
It'd be wrong of me
to fall ill again.

255
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:13,539
I wouldn't do that to those...

256
00:17:14,539 --> 00:17:16,809
who took care of me when I could
barely stand on my feet.

257
00:17:28,619 --> 00:17:30,119
Our goal is...

258
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:33,660
to conceal how
we're not blood-related.

259
00:17:34,759 --> 00:17:38,200
My role is to be
a good mother to you...

260
00:17:39,730 --> 00:17:42,769
while your role is to be
the perfect son now.

261
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,269
Don't forget that.

262
00:17:45,970 --> 00:17:49,269
It's the only reason
I'm letting you stay in this family.

263
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:51,710
I have...

264
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:55,079
nothing but gratitude.

265
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:59,549
Also, I dearly...

266
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:02,990
love you, Mom.

267
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:16,930
Aren't you sick and tired
of this game of 20 years?

